Reasoning: The paper focuses on the concept of mutational robustness in software, which is a key aspect of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of test cases and mutation operators from genetic programming suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The study of software behavior and its ability to withstand random mutations may also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The idea of leveraging neutral mutations for generating software diversity and repairing bugs suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the study of software vulnerabilities and the potential for exploiting neutral mutations may also fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
